-- Exxon, Shell could request SPR loans: Louisiana Gov.
-- 
-- Tue Sep 2, 2008 11:05am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/02/us-storm-gustav-energy-spr-idUSN0239615720080902

 

 HOUSTON  (Reuters) - Exxon Mobil Corp ( XOM.N ) and Shell Oil ( RDSa.L ) could submit formal requests to the Energy Department on Tuesday for emergency crude oil loans from the U.S. stockpile to offset potential shortages from Hurricane Gustav, Louisiana Gov. Bobby Jindal said. 

 (Reporting by  Chris Baltimore )